{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2f27260a-6c94-4268-90e8-e777ceffe844","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changes\n\nThe old VSTest `--filter` uses `&` for AND. The MTP runner uses `--filter` too, but the syntax differs:\n\n**Old (VSTest / xunit v2):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**New (MTP / xunit v3):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nActually the **filter expression itself** is the same here — MTP supports the same `~` (contains), `=`, and `&` operators for `FullyQualifiedName` and trait properties. However, there's a critical difference:\n\n### 2. `--filter` must be passed *to the test executable*, not to `dotnet test`\n\nWith `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true`, `dotnet test` forwards args, but you can also run the executable directly. The key gotcha is that **`dotnet test` with MTP requires `--` to forward filter args** in some configurations:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nOr run the built executable directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet build\n./bin/Debug/net8.0/TestProject --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n### 3. Trait filtering difference\n\nIn xUnit v3 with MTP, trait filtering uses `trait-name=value` syntax instead of just `Category=Smoke`. You may need:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThe trait name `Category` stays the same because that's what `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` defines — so the filter string itself doesn't change. But if it's not working, try the **`--treenode-filter`** option specific to xUnit v3:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --treenode-filter \"/*/*/IntegrationTests/*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n### TL;DR\n\nUpdate your CI to:\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThe `--` separator ensures the filter reaches the MTP runner.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0ab82336-361d-4f57-b09f-74521d740f5c","outputTokens":591,"requestId":"680F:15FC40:77024A:7E797E:6A044DC6"},"id":"8748d27c-5ff5-4ddf-a46a-eecf47f5456a","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:09:24.044Z","parentId":"bed25781-5037-459b-9e2d-c702ff0aa222"}
